,"text":"Return Value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This version of "},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" requires the usage of the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Presents()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" macro and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type in your feature’s domain."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if a parent feature holds onto a piece of optional child state, then it can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"perform its core logic "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the child’s logic by using the "},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  @ObservableState","  struct State {","    @Presents var child: Child.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(PresentationAction<Child.Action>)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some ReducerOf<Self> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifLet(\\.$child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ifLet"},{"type":"text","text":" operator does a number of things to make integrating parent and child features"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ergonomic and enforce correctness:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction\/dismiss","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent, it runs the parent feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"before the child state is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’d out. This gives the parent feature an opportunity to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inspect the child state one last time before the state is cleared."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction\/presented(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":" action is sent it runs the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the parent feature to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":"’d","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"out.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automatically "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s out child state when an